D. Acquisition Strategy
The SBX is contractor-operated and maintained through various contracts held by MDA, as well as the Navy's Military Sealift Command (MSC).

The MDA SBX program office manages 3 Prime contracts for Software Development/Maintenance; Operations & Sustainment (O&S); and Mission Integration. The
acquisition strategy for X-Band Radar (XBR) Software development and Contractor Logistics Support was approved by the MDA Director on July 22, 2016, authorizing
the Ground Sensors (SN) directorate to award sole source Indefinite Delivery/Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) contracts for follow-on development and logistics support to The
Raytheon Company. The Radar Development Contract (RDC) IDIQ was awarded November 1, 2017, for Systems Engineering, software and hardware development,
software maintenance, and Subject Matter Expertise (SME) support to integration and test. SBX has awarded Task Orders (TOs) against this contract vehicle since
IDIQ contract award, with the most recent being Task Order 0008 (HQ0862-23-F-0004) on November 1, 2023, with a Period of Performance extending to October 31,
2027 if all option periods are exercised. The Contractor Logistics Support (CLS) IDIQ contract was also awarded on November 1, 2017, for O&S, logistics, spares
management, and associated support of fielded radar systems. Similar to software development, the SBX program has awarded Task Orders for continued O&S
of the XBR aboard the SBX since the IDIQ was awarded with the most recent being the award of FY 2025 - FY 2026 support (HQ0862-21-F-0002) on October 31,

