2024, for continued O&S support through October 31, 2026. Lastly, the SBX product office holds a Mission Integration contract to fully integrate all aspects of the SBX
program across all payloads to ensure Homeland Defense and Space Domain Awareness mission readiness. The Mission Integration contract (HQ0862-25-C-0001) is
a competitively awarded, Woman-owned Small Business (WOSB) effort that was awarded on October 25, 2024, with a total PoP through October 24, 2029, if all option
periods are exercised.


The Navy's MSC maintains contracts for SBX-1 Vessel Management and Operations; Offshore Supply Vessel; and Security. The SBX-1 was officially transitioned
and transferred to the U.S. Navy on December 22, 2011. Since then, MSC has been responsible for ensuring vessel readiness, vessel lifecycle management and
maintenance/repair, availability and operation of the Operational Support Vessel, transportation and vessel logistics support, security services, and technical SME
support for SBX-1 vessel systems. MSC manages all aspects of contract planning, award, and execution for these services. The MDA maintains financial responsibility
for all SBX-1 support and provides funding for these services via Military Interdepartmental Purchase Request (MIPR).




