Congressional Add: Atmospheric River Research                                                                              0.000   2.500
FY 2024 Accomplishments: N/A
FY 2025 Plans: The Navy will work with the Scripps Institution of Oceanography as the central institution to
support applied S&T observing, modeling, and logistics coordination for field work in the Study of Air-sea Fluxes
and Atmospheric River Intensity (SAFARI) Directed Research Initiative. SAFARI intends to increase the Navy's
understanding of the physical processes associated with air-sea interaction and diabatic amplification (in which
energy is transported through latent heating due to water vapor transport) that perturb the waveguide along
sloping mid-latitude fronts interacting with warm water vapor reservoirs in the tropics, which in turn leads to
strong baroclinic development in maritime midlatitude storms and additionally can launch deep propagating
Rossby and gravity waves into the stratosphere. This multi-agency, international effort will result in better
understanding the role of ocean surface variability and vertical or slant-wise transport of moisture by focusing on
upstream development in atmospheric river source regions to ultimately improve prediction lead-time of extreme
precipitation.
