        Funding: $106.201M increase due to DoD Implementation of PE Consolidation stemming from the Commission on PPBE Interim Report. The PE consolidation
        groups technology projects to allow flexibility that would foster innovation and promote efficiency while empowering prioritization of technologies in support
        of capability gaps identified in Program of Records (PoR) and warfighting areas with no loss of transparency. The Innovative Naval Prototypes (INP) Applied
        Research (6.2) PE 0602792N has been consolidated into the Future Naval Capabilities Applied Research (6.2) PE 0602750N beginning in FY2026 with
        retainment of the prior FNC project structure by focus area for alignment to SECNAV's S&T Strategy.

        A new project structure was created to promote greater transparency and execution oversight for the 6.2 applied research Future Naval Capabilities Technology
        Candidates and Innovative Naval Prototypes in the Department of the Navy's annual budget request. New Projects units (PUs) 1502, 1503, 1505, 1506, 1507,
        1508 and 5891 were created in this PE and were previously funded in PE, 0602750N, in PUs 1385, 1386, 1388, 1389, 1391, 1392, 1393, 1395, 1398, 1399, 1401
        and 5893 and in PE 0602792N PUs 3456, 3463, 3507, 5891, 5899 and 5901. These are not new starts.


